This paper proposes a novel CDN architecture that utilizes Information-Centric Networks (ICN) routing function to route edge-to-edge transactions. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-category. Additionally, the paper addresses the resource placement problem, which falls under the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of algorithms, which could place it under the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The paper discusses the efficiency of the proposed architecture, which could place it under the Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) sub-category. Finally, the paper proposes a solution to a specific problem, which could place it under the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category.
